<br>
I started out with a 1989 Mustang LX when I was 16, and if it wasn't a 4 cylinder car who knows what trouble I would have gotten into. I worked in a Ford dealership for a few years and had parents come in and buy their teen drivers brand new Mustang GTs. I know that there are a lot of responsible teens out there, but I want more parents to be educated before they put their kids behind the wheel of any high-powered car.<br>
<br>
Below I have posted quite a few links to Mustang wrecks involving younger drivers. This is an issue that I have been concerned with for a while and feel better for sharing it. If it saves even one life its worth it.<br>
<br>
